{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Cook elbow macaroni in a large saucepan on the stove as per package directions. Rinse in Varoma dish, transfer to a casserole dish (12 in. x 10 in. x 2 in.) and set aside. Meanwhile, preheat oven to 350°F.","Place 8 oz cheddar cheese and 1 oz Parmesan cheese into mixing bowl and grate <nobr>5 sec\/speed 8<\/nobr>. Sprinkle cheese mixture over macaroni in casserole dish and spread evenly using spatula.","Place 8 oz Emmental cheese and 1 oz Parmesan cheese into mixing bowl and grate <nobr>7 sec\/speed 8<\/nobr>. Sprinkle cheese mixture over macaroni in casserole dish and spread evenly using spatula.","Place milk, flour, 3 oz butter, salt and Tabasco into the mixing bowl and cook <nobr>10 min\/195°F\/speed 4<\/nobr>. Transfer sauce onto macaroni and cheese in casserole dish and mix through with a spoon.","Place 0.5 oz butter and cornflakes into mixing bowl and mix <nobr>5 sec\/speed 4.5<\/nobr>. Sprinkle cornflakes over macaroni and cheese, bake for 25 minutes (350°F) until bubbly and cornflakes have browned. Serve hot."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["16 oz elbow macaroni","8 oz cheddar cheese, cubed (1 in.)","2 oz Parmesan cheese, cubed (1 in.), divided","8 oz Emmental cheese, cubed (1 in.)","26 oz whole milk","3 tbsp all-purpose flour","3 ½ oz unsalted butter, in pieces, divided","1 tsp salt","2 tsp Tabasco (see Tip)","3 oz cornflakes, crushed"]}],"id":"r91346","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-D9fjwNGJWow\/XZMzOlUlzyI\/AAAAAAAAauw\/u5gj2rlptgkQFNlmcgrthpb7jLrSsKZBACLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_YSVBFQaXcSbBYV9m.png","title":"Macaroni and Cheese","publishedAt":"2017-03-24T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"34 g","fat":"41 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"54 g","calories":"3017 kJ \/ 721 kcal"},"usefulItems":"casserole dish (12 in. x 10 in. x 2 in.), large saucepan, oven","hintsAndTricks":["Pasta that is cooked al dente is tender but still firm to the bite.","Tabasco can be reduced to 1 tsp.","Replace Emmental cheese with cheddar cheese."],"basicInfo":["easy","10m","35m","6 portion"]}